---
import DocsLayout from "~/layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Introduction"
  description="Documentation for budi — the open-source, local-first cost tracker for AI coding agents like Cursor, Claude Code, Codex, and Copilot Chat."
>
  <div class="flex max-w-2xl flex-col gap-8">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">Documentation</h1>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Budi is an open-source, local-first cost tracker for AI coding agents. It tails the
        transcript files your tools already write to disk — nothing in your network path.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 id="what-budi-does" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        What budi does
      </h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
        After a single install command, three things run on your machine: a small Rust daemon that
        tails transcripts, a status bar in your editor, and a CLI for repo / branch / ticket
        attribution. Budi tracks Claude Code, Codex CLI, Copilot CLI, Cursor, and Copilot Chat (VS
        Code) today — with more agents coming.
      </p>
      <ul class="text-fg-muted mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span
            ><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Multi-agent</strong> — one daemon tracks all your AI
            coding tools at once.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span
            ><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Real attribution</strong> — cost is attributed per repo,
            branch, and ticket.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span
            ><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Privacy-first</strong> — prompts, code, and responses
            never leave your machine.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          <span
            ><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Online dashboard</strong> — opt-in, syncs aggregates
            only.</span
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="quick-start" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Quick start
      </h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted leading-relaxed">
        Install budi with one command, then verify with <code
          class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
          >budi doctor</code
        >. The <a href="/docs/getting-started/" class="link-underline hover:text-fg"
          >Getting started</a
        > guide walks through every step.
      </p>
      <div class="card mt-4 overflow-hidden">
        <pre
          class="terminal-scroll text-fg m-0 overflow-x-auto px-4 py-4 text-[12px] leading-[1.55] sm:text-[13px]"><code>{`brew install siropkin/budi/budi && budi init
budi integrations install
budi doctor`}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="docs-overview" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        What's in the docs
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <a
          href="/docs/getting-started/"
          class="card hover:border-accent group flex flex-col gap-2 p-5 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-fg group-hover:text-accent font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors"
          >
            Getting started
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Install, initialize, wire up your editor, and verify everything works.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/docs/providers/"
          class="card hover:border-accent group flex flex-col gap-2 p-5 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-fg group-hover:text-accent font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors"
          >
            Providers
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Which AI coding agents budi tracks, how data is sourced, and what's coming next.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/docs/commands/"
          class="card hover:border-accent group flex flex-col gap-2 p-5 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-fg group-hover:text-accent font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors"
          >
            Commands
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            CLI reference for stats, sessions, doctor, status, and more.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/privacy"
          class="card hover:border-accent group flex flex-col gap-2 p-5 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-fg group-hover:text-accent font-semibold tracking-tight transition-colors"
          >
            Privacy & Data Contract
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Full technical contract for what data leaves your machine and what never does.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
